There are days which occur in this
climate, at almost any season of the
year, wherein the world reaches its
perfection, when the air, the heavenly
bodies, and the earth, make a harmony,
as if nature would indulge her
offspring; when, in these bleak upper
sides of the planet, nothing is to desire
that we have heard of the happiest
latitudes, and we bask in the shining
hours of Utah and Colorado; when
everything that has life gives sign of
satisfaction, and the cattle that lie on
the ground seem to have great and
tranquil thoughts.
